{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "a6ef71c6-a514-45f9-bd82-f7f12962a76a",
		"name": "API-Go REST-Chaining",
		"description": "This collection demonstrates **API chaining** using the **Go Rest API** ([<code><b>https://gorest.co.in/public/v2/users</b></code>](https://gorest.co.in/public/v2/users)).\n\n**API chaining** refers to using data from one API response (such as a token or ID) as input for subsequent API requests.\n\nIn this collection:\n\n- `gorest_url` is stored in an **collection** variable.\n    \n- A **token is generated using** [Get your access token ](https://gorest.co.in/my-account/access-tokens) Login into it > Token is created and stored in an **collection** variable.\n    \n- The stored token is then used to authorize **CREATE**, **POST, PUT, and DELETE** requests.\n    \n- A **dynamic** `name, email` is generated in the **Pre-request Script** and saved as a **collection variable**.\n    \n- The `user_id` returned from the user creation response is stored as a **collection variable** in the **Post-response script.**\n    \n- This stored `user_id` is reused to:\n    \n    - **Read** the order using **GET**\n        \n    - **Update** the order using **PUT**\n        \n    - **Delete** the order using **DELETE**\n        \n- Also in **DELETE** all the collection variable are **unset**.\n    \n- Basic validation at **REQUEST** level is done(status code, response data).",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "21963655"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Create User",
			"event": [
				{
					"listen": "test",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"const jsonData = pm.response.json();\r",
							"pm.test(\"Status code is 201\", function () {\r",
							"    pm.response.to.have.status(201);\r",
							"    pm.collectionVariables.set(\"user_id\", jsonData.id);\r",
							"    let user_id = pm.collectionVariables.get(\"user_id\");\r",
							"    let user_name = pm.collectionVariables.get(\"name\");\r",
							"    let user_email = pm.collectionVariables.get(\"email\");\r",
							"    console.log(user_id+\" \"+user_name+\" \"+user_email);\r",
							"});\r",
							""
						],
						"type": "text/javascript",
						"packages": {},
						"requests": {}
					}
				},
				{
					"listen": "prerequest",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"function randomString(length){\r",
							"    return Math.random().toString(36).substring(2, 2 + length);\r",
							"}\r",
							"let name = randomString(6);\r",
							"let email = `${name}@test.com`;\r",
							"\r",
							"pm.collectionVariables.set(\"name\", name);\r",
							"pm.collectionVariables.set(\"email\", email);"
						],
						"type": "text/javascript",
						"packages": {},
						"requests": {}
					}
				}
			],
			"request": {
				"auth": {
					"type": "bearer",
					"bearer": [
						{
							"key": "token",
							"value": "{{gorest_token}}",
							"type": "string"
						}
					]
				},
				"method": "POST",
				"header": [],
				"body": {
					"mode": "raw",
					"raw": "{\r\n    \"name\": \"{{name}}\",\r\n    \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\r\n    \"gender\": \"female\",\r\n    \"status\": \"active\"\r\n}",
					"options": {
						"raw": {
							"language": "json"
						}
					}
				},
				"url": {
					"raw": "{{gorest_url}}/public/v2/users",
					"host": [
						"{{gorest_url}}"
					],
					"path": [
						"public",
						"v2",
						"users"
					]
				}
			},
			"response": []
		},
		{
			"name": "Read User",
			"event": [
				{
					"listen": "test",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {\r",
							"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
							"});\r",
							"\r",
							"pm.test(\"Response data validation\", function()  {\r",
							"    const jsonData = pm.response.json();\r",
							"    pm.expect(jsonData.id).to.have.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get(\"user_id\"));\r",
							"    pm.expect(jsonData.name).to.have.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get(\"name\"));\r",
							"    pm.expect(jsonData.email).to.have.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get(\"email\"));\r",
							"});"
						],
						"type": "text/javascript",
						"packages": {},
						"requests": {}
					}
				}
			],
			"protocolProfileBehavior": {
				"disableBodyPruning": true
			},
			"request": {
				"auth": {
					"type": "bearer",
					"bearer": [
						{
							"key": "token",
							"value": "{{gorest_token}}",
							"type": "string"
						}
					]
				},
				"method": "GET",
				"header": [],
				"body": {
					"mode": "raw",
					"raw": "",
					"options": {
						"raw": {
							"language": "json"
						}
					}
				},
				"url": {
					"raw": "{{gorest_url}}/public/v2/users/{{user_id}}",
					"host": [
						"{{gorest_url}}"
					],
					"path": [
						"public",
						"v2",
						"users",
						"{{user_id}}"
					]
				}
			},
			"response": []
		},
		{
			"name": "Update User",
			"event": [
				{
					"listen": "prerequest",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"function randomString(length){\r",
							"    return Math.random().toString(36).substring(2, 2 + length);\r",
							"}\r",
							"let name = randomString(6);\r",
							"let email = `${name}@test.com`;\r",
							"\r",
							"pm.collectionVariables.set(\"name\", name);\r",
							"pm.collectionVariables.set(\"email\", email);"
						],
						"type": "text/javascript",
						"packages": {},
						"requests": {}
					}
				},
				{
					"listen": "test",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {\r",
							"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);\r",
							"});"
						],
						"type": "text/javascript",
						"packages": {},
						"requests": {}
					}
				}
			],
			"request": {
				"method": "PUT",
				"header": [],
				"body": {
					"mode": "raw",
					"raw": "{\r\n    \"name\": \"{{name}}\",\r\n    \"email\": \"{{email}}\"\r\n}\r\n\r\n",
					"options": {
						"raw": {
							"language": "json"
						}
					}
				},
				"url": {
					"raw": "{{gorest_url}}/public/v2/users/{{user_id}}",
					"host": [
						"{{gorest_url}}"
					],
					"path": [
						"public",
						"v2",
						"users",
						"{{user_id}}"
					]
				}
			},
			"response": []
		},
		{
			"name": "Delete User",
			"event": [
				{
					"listen": "test",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"pm.test(\"Status code is 200 or 204\", function () {\r",
							"    pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.have.oneOf([200, 204]);\r",
							"});\r",
							"\r",
							"pm.collectionVariables.unset(\"user_id\");\r",
							"pm.collectionVariables.unset(\"name\");\r",
							"pm.collectionVariables.unset(\"email\");\r",
							""
						],
						"type": "text/javascript",
						"packages": {},
						"requests": {}
					}
				}
			],
			"request": {
				"method": "DELETE",
				"header": [],
				"url": {
					"raw": "{{gorest_url}}/public/v2/users/{{user_id}}",
					"host": [
						"{{gorest_url}}"
					],
					"path": [
						"public",
						"v2",
						"users",
						"{{user_id}}"
					]
				}
			},
			"response": []
		}
	],
